Back, where developers

00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:03.330
strike back show.

00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:05.870
This week, however, we're
not doing any of that.

00:01:05.870 --> 00:01:08.660
Because of the massive technical
failures that

00:01:08.660 --> 00:01:11.870
plagued the guys in Mountain
View for the Friday app

00:01:11.870 --> 00:01:16.670
clinic, we decided to take a
slightly different approach to

00:01:16.670 --> 00:01:18.030
this episode today.

00:01:18.030 --> 00:01:19.080
So today, we're going
to be talking

00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:21.610
about responsive design.

00:01:21.610 --> 00:01:25.260
So let's jump into what
responsive design is.

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:27.860
Now, for several people, this
is the first time they're

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:31.710
hearing of the concept
of responsive design.

00:01:31.710 --> 00:01:33.150
And Ethan Marcotte--

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:35.500
and sorry, Ethan, if I'm
mispronouncing your name--

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:39.610
Ethan Marcotte coined the term
a few years ago in an article

00:01:39.610 --> 00:01:42.030
that talked about responsive
web design.

00:01:42.030 --> 00:01:43.970
And basically, you can see from
the quote here-- this is

00:01:43.970 --> 00:01:45.260
from the article--

00:01:45.260 --> 00:01:48.500
it's really about taking a
website and making sure that

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:53.110
it scales across any medium, be
it phone, tablet, browser,

00:01:53.110 --> 00:01:57.340
different screen sizes,
and pretty much any

00:01:57.340 --> 00:01:58.580
other device type.

00:01:58.580 --> 00:02:02.930
So taking a single layout or a
single piece of content and

00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:05.680
making sure that it scales
according to its medium.

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:07.870
So that's responsive
web design in

00:02:07.870 --> 00:02:10.580
a super small nutshell.

00:02:10.580 --> 00:02:14.520
So responsive web design
applies to

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:15.970
mobile apps, as well.

00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:17.680
And so today, we're going to
be talking about responsive

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:22.130
design and how it applies
to Android devices.

00:02:22.130 --> 00:02:24.590
Before we jump in, Adam,
Nick, any comments?

00:02:24.590 --> 00:02:26.672
Any thoughts?

00:02:26.672 --> 00:02:29.720
NICK BUTCHER: Yeah, as you were
saying, we're focusing on

00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:32.110
responsive design, because this
week, we're having a big

00:02:32.110 --> 00:02:33.000
focus on tablets.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.250
We've just launched some quality
guidelines on how to

00:02:36.250 --> 00:02:38.300
