Nick, you want to talk a little
bit about Pattrn?

00:08:22.375 --> 00:08:23.070
NICK BUTCHER: Sure.

00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:27.410
So Pattrn is a great little app
for finding wallpapers for

00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:29.820
your device.

00:08:29.820 --> 00:08:33.935
It's by a UK developer called
Lucas who works for Mozilla.

00:08:33.935 --> 00:08:36.809
And I think they've done a great
job of really making the

00:08:36.809 --> 00:08:39.059
content adapt.

00:08:39.059 --> 00:08:41.740
Luckily for them, they have
almost a dream application for

00:08:41.740 --> 00:08:44.860
this kind of scenario where the
content-- the patterned

00:08:44.860 --> 00:08:46.280
wallpapers--

00:08:46.280 --> 00:08:49.290
have no kind of concept
of aspect ratio or

00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:49.820
anything like that.

00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:52.540
They actually kind of tile, so
it works really well that they

00:08:52.540 --> 00:08:55.180
can change for different aspect
ratios, which might not

00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:56.670
be the case for some apps.

00:08:56.670 --> 00:09:00.710
But as you can see, in the three
screens we're showing

00:09:00.710 --> 00:09:04.190
here, on the phone, they're
relying on three tabs to go

00:09:04.190 --> 00:09:07.150
through the three major
views of the data.

00:09:07.150 --> 00:09:09.310
But when they get beyond a
certain point and have more

00:09:09.310 --> 00:09:11.600
space, they actually break that
out away from the tab

00:09:11.600 --> 00:09:15.810
navigation into having this
sidebar, which I think works

00:09:15.810 --> 00:09:16.600
really well.

00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:18.760
Rather than just stretching the
content to be overly wide,

00:09:18.760 --> 00:09:24.950
it actually gives you easier
navigation, as well as

00:09:24.950 --> 00:09:26.130
servicing more information.

00:09:26.130 --> 00:09:28.350
So you can see there on the
Nexus 7, for example, it

00:09:28.350 --> 00:09:30.030
services recent searches.

00:09:30.030 --> 00:09:31.720
So it's kind of one tap away.

00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:33.990
Rather than having to tap into
the search field and then get

00:09:33.990 --> 00:09:36.260
shown the recent history, it
might prompt you to click on a

00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:39.230
recent search, which
is really great.

00:09:39.230 --> 00:09:40.970
The other thing, if you look
at the difference between,

00:09:40.970 --> 00:09:43.350
say, the phone and the 7-inch
tablet, is they've actually

00:09:43.350 --> 00:09:47.320
