00:11:54.340 --> 00:11:55.120
good things.

00:11:55.120 --> 00:12:00.020
So this is kind of the main
screen in Pocket that lets you

00:12:00.020 --> 00:12:02.250
see the list of your
saved articles.

00:12:02.250 --> 00:12:06.270
So you'll see that on the phone,
they have a simple list

00:12:06.270 --> 00:12:08.410
with thumbnails on the right.

00:12:08.410 --> 00:12:11.970
Now, when you scale that up to
a 7-inch tablet, they have a

00:12:11.970 --> 00:12:14.710
two-column grid, and if you turn
that over into landscape,

00:12:14.710 --> 00:12:16.830
you'll see that there's
a three-column grid.

00:12:16.830 --> 00:12:19.570
And you'll notice that it's
completely different, but it's

00:12:19.570 --> 00:12:20.730
the same content, right?

00:12:20.730 --> 00:12:24.990
It's more of like a tile view
rather than a simple

00:12:24.990 --> 00:12:27.510
horizontal linear layout.

00:12:27.510 --> 00:12:29.300
And then if you look at the
10-inch tablet, they've

00:12:29.300 --> 00:12:32.200
basically graduated into more
of a quote, unquote,

00:12:32.200 --> 00:12:36.370
"magazine" layout, similar to
how the Google Play client

00:12:36.370 --> 00:12:39.560
application lays out the
different tiles in the

00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:41.090
featured sections.

00:12:41.090 --> 00:12:44.520
So the interesting thing to me
is that they've done a lot of

00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:47.300
work here to tweak font sizes.

00:12:47.300 --> 00:12:51.560
So you'll notice that the title
sizes on the 10-inch

00:12:51.560 --> 00:12:55.130
tablet are slightly larger than
on the 7-inch tablet.

00:12:55.130 --> 00:12:58.110
And then the fact that they've
basically implemented this

00:12:58.110 --> 00:13:02.000
layout three times, once as a
list, another as a grid view,

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:06.920
which is probably a simplified
version of the magazine layout

00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:07.710
on the right.

00:13:07.710 --> 00:13:10.060
But they also have the magazine
layout, which we

00:13:10.060 --> 00:13:11.950
don't have framework
support for.

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:13.850
One of the things I should note
is that they may have

00:13:13.850 --> 00:13:14.630
cheated a little bit.

00:13:14.630 --> 00:13:19.150
They may be using WebView in
HTML5 and CSS3 stuff to do the

00:13:19.150 --> 00:13:22.160
layout, which is perfectly
awesome.

00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:24.800
The only issue is that there's
some minor performance

00:13:24.800 --> 00:13:25.310
penalties--

00:13:25.310 --> 00:13:27.490
well, maybe not minor, but there
are some performance

00:13:27.490 --> 00:13:28.940
penalties involved.

00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:33.140
But overall, it looks
just wonderful.

00:13:33.140 --> 00:13:34.910
Yeah, so that's in a nutshell.

00:13:34.910 --> 00:13:36.670
The other thing I wanted to
mention is that they kept the

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:37.930
action bar the same.

00:13:37.930 --> 00:13:39.640
And this is totally fine.

00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:43.040
You don't necessarily have to
switch the action bar and make

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:44.630
it taller, make things wider.

00:13:44.630 --> 00:13:47.640
The framework actually does
all those things for you.

00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:51.690
It'll make your icon slightly
wider, the action

00:13:51.690 --> 00:13:52.940
bar slightly taller.

00:13:52.940 --> 00:13:54.150
So it'll do all those
things for you.

00:13:54.150 --> 00:13:56.580
In this case, I think that
they've probably implemented a

00:13:56.580 --> 00:13:58.300
custom action bar, so it's
not happening there.

00:13:58.300 --> 00:14:02.110
But note that the action bar is
pretty much the same across

00:14:02.110 --> 00:14:05.320
tablet and phone, in terms
of behavior and rough

00:14:05.320 --> 00:14:07.856
proportions.

00:14:07.856 --> 00:14:09.540
NICK BUTCHER: One of my favorite
things that they've

00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:12.720
done on here as well is that you
can see on the phone and

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.630
tablet, they've prioritized the
search, bringing it out

00:14:15.630 --> 00:14:17.920
right at the top of the content
view so you can search

00:14:17.920 --> 00:14:21.520
and filter, whereas on the
tablet, they have kind of

00:14:21.520 --> 00:14:22.870
demoted that.

00:14:22.870 --> 00:14:23.500
So less important.

00:14:23.500 --> 00:14:27.150
I think it's under the action
overflow there, which I think

00:14:27.150 --> 00:14:28.000
is really interesting.

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.850
I think it's shown that they've
thought about how

00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:32.480
someone's going to use this
application slightly

00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:35.590
differently on a tablet, that
they have the same content

00:14:35.590 --> 00:14:37.440
available, but it's a different
representation.

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:40.980
They're kind of designing for
a different use case where

00:14:40.980 --> 00:14:43.665
someone might have more time
and might be in more of an

00:14:43.665 --> 00:14:44.915
explorative mode.

00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:49.330
ROMAN NURIK: Any
other comments?

00:14:49.330 --> 00:14:50.870
OK, so let's move on to--

