00:18:23.990 --> 00:18:24.875
That's TED.

00:18:24.875 --> 00:18:26.935
ROMAN NURIK: OK, so let's
move on to, I

00:18:26.935 --> 00:18:27.920
believe, the last app.

00:18:27.920 --> 00:18:30.300
So we're kind of cheating here,
because this is an app

00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:32.700
that we all worked on.

00:18:32.700 --> 00:18:35.610
This is the Google I/O
2012 application.

00:18:35.610 --> 00:18:38.280
So basically, this app, if you
attended the conference, it

00:18:38.280 --> 00:18:42.240
lets you see what sessions
are playing.

00:18:42.240 --> 00:18:44.980
It lets you create a
personalized schedule.

00:18:44.980 --> 00:18:47.330
It also syncs across your
different devices, which,

00:18:47.330 --> 00:18:51.420
again, is very important for a
multi-device user that has

00:18:51.420 --> 00:18:55.760
multiple devices, having
seamless sync across those.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:58.220
So what we've done here
is basically--

00:18:58.220 --> 00:19:01.150
on phone, there isn't that
much horizontal space.

00:19:01.150 --> 00:19:06.060
So we have three tabs for the
different core pieces of

00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:07.010
functionality.

00:19:07.010 --> 00:19:09.610
That's kind of the interaction
side where you interact with

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:11.980
other people on Google+ that
are also attending the

00:19:11.980 --> 00:19:13.140
conference.

00:19:13.140 --> 00:19:16.890
The My Schedule or My Agenda
area, and then the exploration

00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:19.970
phase, where you can look at
the map or take a look at

00:19:19.970 --> 00:19:23.020
individual tracks.

00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:25.290
So the interesting thing that
we've done here is we split it

00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:30.110
up from tabs to multiple
panes across tablets.

00:19:30.110 --> 00:19:32.600
So in portrait, actually,
both of these devices--

00:19:32.600 --> 00:19:34.520
7-inch and the 10-inch
device--

00:19:34.520 --> 00:19:38.670
in portrait, they would show
this kind of two-column

00:19:38.670 --> 00:19:42.180
layout, where two of the panes
are stacked in one column.

00:19:42.180 --> 00:19:46.660
And in the landscape, they
switch to a wider

00:19:46.660 --> 00:19:48.560
