00:21:52.140 --> 00:21:56.640
OK, so let's move on to the
second screen in this app.

00:21:56.640 --> 00:21:59.930
And this is basically the
session detail screen.

00:21:59.930 --> 00:22:05.140
So once I get into a specific
session, like in this case,

00:22:05.140 --> 00:22:08.510
the session that Chris and Ellie
gave on Android apps and

00:22:08.510 --> 00:22:09.590
Google Play where they
announced the

00:22:09.590 --> 00:22:11.500
new publisher console.

00:22:11.500 --> 00:22:14.100
Once I get into the screen,
there's a bunch of information

00:22:14.100 --> 00:22:15.890
that I may want to see, a bunch
of actions that I may

00:22:15.890 --> 00:22:17.370
want to take on the session.

00:22:17.370 --> 00:22:19.510
For example, I may want to add
it or remove it from my

00:22:19.510 --> 00:22:23.430
schedule, share it with people,
see a map of it,

00:22:23.430 --> 00:22:24.030
things like that.

00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:25.840
I may want to +1 it up here.

00:22:25.840 --> 00:22:28.360
And I may want to see the list
of speakers, learn more about

00:22:28.360 --> 00:22:31.370
Chris or Ellie, and
then there's a few

00:22:31.370 --> 00:22:33.360
links at the bottom.

00:22:33.360 --> 00:22:37.750
So what we've done here is this
is a single screen on--

00:22:37.750 --> 00:22:40.020
well, the session detail and the
list of sessions, which is

00:22:40.020 --> 00:22:41.740
a previous screen.

00:22:41.740 --> 00:22:45.145
This is a single screen on
phones, whereas on tablets,

00:22:45.145 --> 00:22:47.550
it's combined into a
multi-pane layout.

00:22:47.550 --> 00:22:53.100
This is kind of the very common
master detail layout

00:22:53.100 --> 00:22:56.200
that's used in almost all
of our system apps.

00:22:56.200 --> 00:22:58.010
You'll notice that
in portrait--

00:22:58.010 --> 00:22:59.330
it's not really visible here.

00:22:59.330 --> 00:23:00.370
We kind of need animations.

00:23:00.370 --> 00:23:03.020
We don't have the fancy
technology to show this.

00:23:03.020 --> 00:23:06.910
But in portrait, it's kind
of a sliding screen.

00:23:06.910 --> 00:23:10.250
So that left pane collapses
once you start interacting

00:23:10.250 --> 00:23:12.310
with the right detail pane.

00:23:12.310 --> 00:23:15.455
And then pressing the Up button
slides it in again, or

00:23:15.455 --> 00:23:17.600
it's just actually sliding
on the screen.

00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:21.430
And then in 10-inch tablets on
landscape, we have all that

00:23:21.430 --> 00:23:24.830
space available, so we don't
need that collapsing behavior.

00:23:24.830 --> 00:23:26.080
So it's always visible.

00:23:29.120 --> 00:23:32.566
Any thoughts, guys, on other
